unquestionably Croatia joining the European Union in July 2013. This has been after mutiple unsuccessful attempts dating back to the 1990s and notwithstanding numerous fail attempts in the past two decades. read more »

At the financial markets witnessing the next move, the Hungarian forint now outperforms the Slovak crown amongst the CEE currencies and the Romanian leu might soon surpass its old time best.

Czech koruna and Polish zloty turned back direct flirting with one or another bilateral limit and are generally depreciating versus the euro around 3.45 where the interest rate differential favors deeply a Czech premium. The European Union Monetary authority got the weaker competitor in the Austrian central bank while banking coaches limited its options.

At first there are 8,4 bn forints in supply and the demand for original papers comes down to 3,2 unnecessary forints – note the chief MNBest dealers. (MNBest=Marko-money Market Best) read more »

Draghi’s speech sent a clear message last week the main interest rate could and would be cut further in a deflationary scenario. Having said that, the worsening of the situation pairs the ECB against the Bundesbank whose head Market Faz said he is for stimulus but against asset purchases.

True stimulus units are given if the Italian and Spanish yields go up.
